International law works only when the parties that craft the law abide by it. The funny thing is, much of international law is not recognized by all of the 300+ countries in the world. Kinda reminds me of the reservation board rofl. <br>
<br>
Therefore, when a government that sponsors, feeds, houses, and takes pride in terrorists, they are outside the framework of &quot;international law&quot; since they never agreed to it in the first place.<br>
Recognizing this big picture will hopefully change the minds of these pro &quot;pacifists&quot; and &quot;legal approach&quot; people. We dont live in a bubble. Ghandi succeeded because he was ousting control of a government that wasnt prepared to annihilate him and all his followers. We dont have that luxury here. Civilians wont be targetted by US military troops, this is a war of small wet ops, and pressuring governments to do their own damn job, namely: Stop harboring terrorists or become a target themselves. <p><br><b>Lilhaer Blackdagger</b>
